    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Special type of roofing tile made with perforations to permit the passage of air and sometimes light. Ventilating tiles are typically set into a span of regular roof tiles; they usually have a raised, curving profile in which the ventilation holes are situated.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
